reviews.review_text: Fabulous Kick-Off for 1970 The beginning of the most important (IMHO) year for the Dead. TC is way up in there, mix-wise. Bear is at the faders and knobs for this very good quality soundboard.

- Starts out great, with nice harmonies, but it never takes off into instrumental wonderfulness. The Dark Star uses a lot of minimalism and negative space, which is an interesting sound art idea but not as fun to listen to as the jams from, say, early '69.

One of the greatest Dark Stars ever recorded? If not, certainly one of my all-time favorites. The jam they embark on after the spacey interlude truly catches fire, and the boys keep it burning through an excellent Feelin Groovy jam, AND THEN top it off with an incendiary Tighten Up jam, peaking multiple times along the way. I believe you can hear Bobby taking a solo during the Tighten Up sequence, and it goes to show what a talented player he was in his own right. An absolutely shining example of the caliber of free form playing these guys were capable of. Gotta love any 1970 show, especially one at the Fillmore. Easilly the peak year for the group IMHO.

Bob dave
Bob was such a talented guitar player. So talented that Jerry and Phil wanted to kick him out of the band for his guitar playing in Oct '68. Just sayin
I love Bob but let's not get carried away
More Phil! It's hard to hear Phil in this recording.
